{"coursehistories": {"path": "/coursehistories/400"}, "description": "This course will look at the screenplay as both a literary text and a blue print for production. Several classic screenplay texts will be critically analyzed (REBEL WITHOUT A CAUSE, DOCTOR STRANGELOVE, PSYCHO, etc.) Students will then embark on writing their own scripts. We will intensively focus on: character enhancement, creating \"believable\" cinematic dialogue, plot development and story structure, conflict, pacing, dramatic foreshadowing, the element of surprise, text and subtext and visual story-telling. Class attendance is mandatory. Students will submit their works-in-progress to the workshop for discussion. \n\nSee English Department's website at www.english.upenn.edu for a description of the current offerings. \n\n", "semester": "2004A", "name": "SCREENWRITING WORKSHOP", "reviews": {"path": "/courses/6434/reviews", "values": [{"ratings": {"rAmountLearned": "3.64", "rDifficulty": "2.45", "rStimulateInterest": "3.91", "rRecommendMajor": "3.82", "rCourseQuality": "3.73", "rWorkRequired": "2.45", "rInstructorAccess": "3.73", "rReadingsValue": "3.36", "rRecommendNonMajor": "3.64", "rCommAbility": "3.73", "rInstructorQuality": "3.82"}, "section": {"name": "SCREENWRITING WORKSHOP", "sectionnum": "401", "primary_alias": "ENGL-116-401", "path": "/courses/6434/sections/401", "id": "6434-401", "aliases": ["ENGL-116-401", "FILM-116-401"]}, "comments": "", "num_students": 12, "path": "/courses/6434/sections/401/reviews/431-MARC-LAPADULA", "instructor": {"path": "/instructors/431-MARC-LAPADULA", "first_name": "MARC", "last_name": "LAPADULA", "id": "431-MARC-LAPADULA", "name": "MARC LAPADULA"}, "num_reviewers": 11, "id": "6434-401-431-MARC-LAPADULA"}, {"ratings": {"rAmountLearned": "3.67", "rDifficulty": "2.33", "rStimulateInterest": "3.92", "rRecommendMajor": "3.92", "rCourseQuality": "3.92", "rWorkRequired": "2.33", "rInstructorAccess": "3.58", "rReadingsValue": "4.00", "rRecommendNonMajor": "3.67",